description: Jackie Denisco tallied 35 digs as the Academy of Notre Dame defeated Nasboba Tech, 3-1, in a Commonwealth Athletic Conference girls volleyball match. Notre Dame 3 Nashoba Tech 1
title: Lancers Get by Vikings
maintext:
Lancers Get by Vikings
Jackie Denisco tallied 35 digs as the Academy of Notre Dame defeated Nasboba Tech, 3-1, in a Commonwealth Athletic Conference girls volleyball match.
Notre Dame 3
Nashoba Tech 1
Elena Murguia had 17 assists and 13 service points as the Lancers topped Nashoba Tech, 22-25, 25-22, 25-13, 25-18.
Girls volleyball
Maddie Walent notched 15 service points with 10 aces. Christina Tasillas chipped in with 5 kills and 2 blocks.
Julie Getchell (3 kills) and Angela Tarantino (2 blocks) played well for NDA.
NDA head coach Richard Sierra was Nashoba Tech’s head coach from 2015-16. This was Sierra’s first matchup as NDA’s head coach against his former team.
Lincoln-Sudbury 3
Westford 0
Lincoln-Sudbury swept past Westford Academy, 25-23, 25-22, 25-20, in a DCL match.
Elise Sepe finished with 7 kills, 2 aces and 3 blocks for Westford (7-6).
Kingswood 3
Pelham 0
Pelham ended the 2018 season with a tough 25-19, 25-22, 26-24 loss to visiting Kingswood Regional.
Ally Altieri led the Pythons, winners of two matches, with 9 assists and 5 digs. Elise Hooper was also solid with 17 service points and 12 digs, while Natalia Villanueva had 4 kills and 6 digs. Also starring were Kate Fisher (5 kills), Maria Dagher (3 blocks) and Hannah Andrewchuck (3 assists).
Greater Lawrence 3
Greater Lowell 2
Kailynn Senechiame served well for Greater Lowell Tech during this CAC match.
Lynna Lopez and Jess Lawler had strong all-around matches.
